fields.manuscript_full_text_std_spelling: O virgo ecclesia plangendum est quod sevissimus lupus filios tuos de latere tuo abstraxit o ve callido serpenti sed o quam preciosus est sanguis salvatoris qui in vexillo regis ecclesiam ipsi desponsavit unde filios illius requirit
fields.indexing_notes: This is a mode 4 antiphon as its incipit goes below the final. Based on a comparison with other antiphons within Hildegard's manuscripts that include differentia, antiphons with incipits that go below the final are plagal modes, whilst those that stay above the final are authentic modes.

fields.manuscript_full_text_std_spelling: Nunc gaudeant materna viscera ecclesiae quia in superna simphonia filii eius in sinum suum collocati sunt unde o turpissime serpens confusus es quoniam quos tua estimatio in visceribus suis habuit nunc fulgent in sanguine filii dei et ideo laus tibi sit rex altissime alleluia
fields.indexing_notes: Possible scribal error in this manuscript ends the antiphon on a B. The same antiphon in B-DEa 9 ends, correctly, on a C. The last two syllables in this manuscript appear to have been erroneously transcribed a step too low.
